SIMPLE: afflatus
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Afflatus
<hw>Af*fla"tus</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr.
<ets>afflare</ets>. See <er>Afflation</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
breath or blast of wind.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A divine impartation of knowledge; supernatural
impulse; inspiration.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A poet writing against his genius will be like a prophet without
his <qex>afflatus</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Spence.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Afflict</ent>⟦br⟧
